<c01 id="aspace_3ed6f63ceb90b176af710bae8743f517" level="file"><did><unittitle>Three repreints of published articles:</unittitle><container id="aspace_bdf59e16bdaae03279d926e44e94e706" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182879]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_5e7eca419d0ed6b7002f063976835f0e" parent="aspace_bdf59e16bdaae03279d926e44e94e706" type="folder">40</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_b0cdb8413d7c7a4c3a8506181b3ce527"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>1. "A Link in the Chain of Events Leading to American Independence," from the <title>William and Mary Quarterly</title>, <date>Jan. 1946</date> </p><p> 2. "The American Doctrine of Containment." <date>1980</date> (2 copies)</p><p> 3. The Origins of the Union and of the States. Separate from the Proceedings of the Massachusettes Historical Society. Vol. 72, (<date>1957-1960</date>)</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_4774b37bb5d1ef6ebc48e6abaa0d5dbd" level="file"><did><unittitle>Twenty-six letters from Curtis Nettels to Van Wyck Brooks, the American author, critic, and translator</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1952/1954" type="inclusive">1952-1954</unitdate><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1958/1963" type="inclusive">1958-1963</unitdate><container id="aspace_22510f628ab1b998891226d7c2e84e8e" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182879]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_55fb0243f5ec597c81e7ad8bda0ab8a5" parent="aspace_22510f628ab1b998891226d7c2e84e8e" type="folder">41</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_f553e296c5fc06ec844358196f5fb445"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>The letters deal mainly with American writers and American literature, some political issues and also discussion of Mr. Brook's books. Some examples of his well known books are: <title>The Wine of the Puritans</title>, <date>1909</date>; <title>America's Coming of Age</title>, <date>1915</date>; <title>The Ordeal of Mark Twain</title>, <date>1920</date>; <title>The Pilgrimage of Henry James</title>, <date>1925</date>; <title>The Life of Emerson</title>, <date>1932</date>; <title>The Flowering of New England</title>, <date>1936</date>; <title>New England: Indian Summer</title>, <date>1940</date>; <title>The World of Washington Irving</title>, <date>1944</date>; <title>The Confident Years</title>, <date>1952</date>; <title>The Writer in America</title>, <date>1953</date>; <title>Helen Keller, Sketch for a Portrait</title>, <date>1956</date>; <title>Days of the Phoenix</title>, 1957</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_fc8ec6aa31972b250d8cc115fcb6a994" level="file"><did><unittitle>Letters</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1952/1952">1952</unitdate><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1959/1959">1959</unitdate><container id="aspace_2b8fa8ab2b1b391600c9253ed01a4213" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182879]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_bae0b7ea91410142bc5dfa0b3f1044d0" parent="aspace_2b8fa8ab2b1b391600c9253ed01a4213" type="folder">42</container></did><scopecontent id="aspace_4cdd80f997a2a46e47e48fedc842f775"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>This folder contains seven photocopies of letters from Van Wyck Brooks to Mr. Nettels. Also, one photocopy of a newspaper clipping written by Curtis Nettels re Van Wyck Brooks</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_c3ffd0e4d76839d70c8edcbef3b44398" level="file"><did><unittitle>One seventy-two page typescript manuscript: "Boyhood Days in a Prarie Town, Memories of Life in Topeka, Kansas, <date>1905-1917</date>," by Curtis Nettels (2 copies)</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" datechar="creation" era="ce" normal="1905/1917" type="inclusive">1905-1917</unitdate><container id="aspace_c54cddc334b2ab33ea518a9fac64b955" label="Mixed Materials [31924065182879]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_d968d92e9840d88a17dbc189ca9d40e5" parent="aspace_c54cddc334b2